{
  "stem": "16345.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And when the-- some of the prisoners were carrying the soup in large kettles, another guy and I-- one of us always was the decoy.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He would run over and make as if he was going to dip his can in the, in the big pot of soup.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then they would start chasing him while I would run over and actually dip my can in the soup.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we would share it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Occasionally when there wasn't-- when they didn't take you out on a work detail, they would, they would have a group of prisoners, let's say, pick rocks from one pile of rocks and carry it a couple of hundred yards down and deposit it in one place.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then they had another group of prisoners take the same rocks and bring them back to the original place to sort of make work and make torture and things like that.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One of my-- of the most vivid stories about Auschwitz was-- that used to give me nightmares, really.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The place was always cold.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I, I don't ever remember being warm in any concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I guess they didn't have any summer in those places.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You'd wake-- I'd wake up in the morning before dawn, because that's where we had to stand on appell, where they counted us.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there was an electrified fence surrounding the, the our camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in the morning, you would take a look and see a bunch of people standing sort of with their arms outstretched, holding on to the electrified fence.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "See, those are the people who couldn't take it anymore.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And, it was always foggy.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
